des:
You can simply ask Alexa to turn on, off, or dim the light. There's no need to go to the switch to adjust your home light - just talk to Alexa on your Amazon Echo.

To take advantage, you will need to connect Alexa to your Smart Garen products by following these simple steps:
(1). Download the "Smart Garen" app from your app store;
(2). Register your account through an address and email or Facebook;
(3). You should have some Smart Garen devices on hand;
(4). Configure your devices in the Smart Garen app and give the names that will be spoken when using the skill.
(5). Download the Amazon app “Alexa” from your app store;
(6). Configure your Alexa device in the application;
(7). Look for the skill " G.Smart " in the Skills tab of the Alexa application;
(8). Click on Enable G.Smart Skill and you will be redirected to the login screen;
(9). Enter your account and password data.
(10). Ready ! The entire configuration is finished;

You are now able to use commands like:
"Alexa, turn on the bedroom light."
"Alexa, turn off the bedroom light."
"Alexa, set the brightness of the room light by 50 percent."
"Alexa, increase the brightness of the room."
"Alexa, dim the room light by 50."
"Alexa, change the room light to green."
"Alexa, set the room lights cooler."
